Organic farmers and ranchers represent the full gamut of American agriculture – from the small operations for farmers markets, to the large producers that supply our global food chains – the USDA Organic Seal covers them all.

The organic market might have been niche in past decades, but it’s now an industry that represents over $50 billion in our food economy. Ensuring that USDA maintains this value-add for producers is important in these uncertain times in agriculture.
There are over 3.5 million breast cancer survivors in the United States. This #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth we reaffirm our commitment to helping people live cancer-free lives.
Each year in the United States, over 252,000 women are diagnosed with breast cancer. Early detection is the key. Be Sure to schedule an annual breast cancer screening. #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth
Did you know? 1 in 8 women in the United States will develop breast cancer in her lifetime. This #BreastCancerAwarenessMonth be sure to speak with your doctor about taking preventative measures.

Investing in disaster recovery and mitigation efforts saves lives and taxpayer money. Too often, when disaster strikes our communities are destroyed, survivors are displaced, and local economies suffer. We must change this and build stronger, more resilient infrastructure.

The U.S. is currently recovering from  10 of the costliest disasters in its history and resources are stretched thin. Tune in live as we explore ways to make coordinating federal recovery programs more efficient, meaning better results for disaster victims.
